And besides, application can also result from all the tools that surround the research.
For example, the same Willard Boyle created a small light sensor in 1969 during his work on optics.
This sensor, although Boyle didn&#39;t initially plan it that way, now serves as the &quot;eye&quot; of all digital cameras in the world and won him the Nobel Prize in Physics in 2009.
